A Flicker in the Dark by Stacy Willingham. Oh my gosh this book had me hooked from the first chapter!

When Chloe Davis was twelve, six teenage girls went missing in her small Louisiana town. By the end of the summer, her own father was arrested and then confessed to the crimes and was put away for life, leaving Chloe and the rest of her family to deal with the truth and try to move forward while dealing with the aftermath.

Now, twenty years later, Chloe is a psychologist and getting ready for her wedding. Then local teenage girls go missing, and that terrifying summer comes crashing back. Is she paranoid? Is there a new killer copying her fathers murders? 

You can’t trust anyone and when you think you know what’s coming next.. you think you’re hit with another twist! #bookclub #bookclubs #bookclubofinstagram #bookclubsofinstagram #bookclubreads #bookclubstagram #bookshelfstyling #bookshelforganization #shelfies #shelfiegoals #shelfielove #bookbloggerbooks #bookbloggersofinstagram

Hook, Line, and Sinker by Tessa Bailey

Rating:⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ .5

I loved Hannah and Fox since their first scene together in It Happened One Summer so, it was great watching it play out. Their friendship was by far the best part of this book.

I think I loved this book more than It Happened One Summer. I love a good friends to lovers and this was a great friends to lovers indeed. The banter in this book was top tier. Overall, if you love slow burn and friends to lovers, I think you would love this book. I wish this series wouldn’t end!
